8 An Act relating to the Office of Management and
Enterprise Services; requiring that portions of
9 certain appropriated funds be used for certain
purposes; mandating certain transfers; requiring
10 utilization in certain manner; providing an effective
date; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. From the funds appropriated to the Office of
16 Management and Enterprise Services in Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1177
17 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of One
18 Million Nine Hundred Twenty Thousand Dollars ($1,920,000.00) shall
19 be used to provide for the Pay for Success program. The Office of
20 Management and Enterprise Services shall transfer the sum of Seven
21 Hundred Twenty Thousand Dollars ($720,000.00) to the Criminal
22 Justice Pay for Success Revolving Fund, created in Section 510.8c of
23 Title 57 of the Oklahoma Statutes, and the sum of One Million Two
24 Hundred Thousand Dollars ($1,200,000.00) to the Pay for Success
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1167 Page 1

1 Inno vation Fund, created in Section 9010.5 of Title 62 of the
2 Oklahoma Statutes.
3 SECTION 2. Of the amount allocated for the Pay for Success
4 program in Section 1 of this act, seventy-five percent (75%) shall
5 be utilized by the Office of Management and Enterprise Services in
6 equal amounts for municipalities of the state with populations of
7 three hundred fifty thousand (350,000) or more as determined by the
8 latest Federal Decennial Census.
9 SECTION 3. There is hereby appropriated to the Central
10 Purchasing Contract Database Revolving Fund, established in Enrolled
11 House Bill No. 3415 of the 2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma
12 Legislature, from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
13 General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal year
14 ending June 30, 2027, the sum of Five Hundred Thousand Dollars
15 ($500,000.00) or so much thereof as may be necessary to carry out
16 the provisions of Enrolled House Bill No. 3415 of the 2nd Session of
17 the 60th Oklahoma Legislature.
18 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
19 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
20 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
21 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
22 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
